<h1 class="firstHeading" id="firstHeading" lang="en">List of United States counties and county equivalents</h1>			<div class="mw-body-content" id="bodyContent">
				<div class="noprint" id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</div>				<div id="contentSub"></div>
				<div id="jump-to-nav"></div>				<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#mw-head">Jump to navigation</a>
				<a class="mw-jump-link" href="#p-search">Jump to search</a>
				<div class="mw-content-ltr" dir="ltr" id="mw-content-text" lang="en"><div class="mw-parser-output"><div class="thumb tright"><div class="thumbinner" style="width:402px;"><a class="image" href="/wiki/File:Usa_counties_large.svg"><img alt="" class="thumbimage" data-file-height="627" data-file-width="990" height="253" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Usa_counties_large.svg/400px-Usa_counties_large.svg.png" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Usa_counties_large.svg/600px-Usa_counties_large.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/59/Usa_counties_large.svg/800px-Usa_counties_large.svg.png 2x" width="400"/></a>  <div class="thumbcaption"><div class="magnify"><a class="internal" href="/wiki/File:Usa_counties_large.svg" title="Enlarge"></a></div>An enlargeable map of the 3,142 <a href="/wiki/County_(United_States)" title="County (United States)">counties</a> and <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/County_equivalent" title="County equivalent">county equivalents</a> located in the 50 states and <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/District_of_Columbia" title="District of Columbia">District of Columbia</a></div></div></div>
<p>This is a complete list of all counties in the United States: 3,142 <a href="/wiki/County_(United_States)" title="County (United States)">counties</a> and county equivalents in the 50 states and <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/District_of_Columbia" title="District of Columbia">District of Columbia</a> as of July 1, 2013<sup class="plainlinks noexcerpt noprint asof-tag update" style="display:none;"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=List_of_United_States_counties_and_county_equivalents&amp;action=edit">[update]</a></sup>, plus an additional 100 county equivalents in the <a href="/wiki/Territories_of_the_United_States" title="Territories of the United States">U.S. territories</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-CensusT_1-0"><a href="#cite_note-CensusT-1">[1]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-CensusCounties2_2-0"><a href="#cite_note-CensusCounties2-2">[2]</a></sup>, for a total of 3,242 counties and county equivalents in the United States. For more detailed information, see the individual state lists <a href="#See_also">shown below</a>.
</p><p>In the United States, a county is a political and geographic subdivision of a state.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-NACO_3-0"><a href="#cite_note-NACO-3">[3]</a></sup> Of the 50 U.S. states, 48 states are divided into a total of 3,007 counties.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_4-0"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-4">[4]</a></sup> The number of counties per state ranges from the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Delaware" title="List of counties in Delaware">three counties</a> in Delaware to the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Texas" title="List of counties in Texas">254 counties</a> in Texas. The <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Rhode_Island" title="List of counties in Rhode Island">five counties</a> in Rhode Island, the <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Connecticut" title="List of counties in Connecticut">eight counties</a> in Connecticut, and <a href="/wiki/List_of_counties_in_Massachusetts" title="List of counties in Massachusetts">eight of the 14 counties</a> in Massachusetts do not have a functional county government, but still exist as legal and census entities.
</p><p>Instead of counties, Louisiana is divided into <a href="/wiki/List_of_parishes_in_Louisiana" title="List of parishes in Louisiana">64 parishes</a> which are functionally similar to counties. Alaska is divided into <a href="/wiki/List_of_boroughs_and_census_areas_in_Alaska" title="List of boroughs and census areas in Alaska">19 organized boroughs</a> and a single <a href="/wiki/Unorganized_Borough,_Alaska" title="Unorganized Borough, Alaska">Unorganized Borough</a>. The <a href="/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau" title="United States Census Bureau">United States Census Bureau</a> has divided the Unorganized Borough of Alaska into 10 census areas for federal census and planning purposes. The <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/List_of_cities_in_Virginia" title="List of cities in Virginia">38 cities</a> in the state of Virginia are <a href="/wiki/Independent_city" title="Independent city">independent cities</a>, which are not considered part of a particular county, and the states of Maryland, Missouri, and Nevada each have one <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">independent city</a> which is not considered part of a particular county. The Census Bureau and the <a href="/wiki/Office_of_Management_and_Budget" title="Office of Management and Budget">Office of Management and Budget</a> consider the 64 parishes, 19 organized boroughs, 10 census areas, 41 independent cities, and the <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">District of Columbia</a>, though not the Unorganized Borough, to be equivalent to counties for statistical purposes.
</p><p><a href="/wiki/Territories_of_the_United_States" title="Territories of the United States">Territories of the United States</a> do not have counties (except for <a href="/wiki/American_Samoa" title="American Samoa">American Samoa</a>, which does have them); instead, the United States Census Bureau divides them into county equivalents. The county equivalents in the territories are the 78 <a href="/wiki/Municipalities_of_Puerto_Rico" title="Municipalities of Puerto Rico">municipalities of Puerto Rico</a>, the 3 main islands of the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/U.S._Virgin_Islands" title="U.S. Virgin Islands">U.S. Virgin Islands</a>, the <a href="/wiki/Administrative_divisions_of_American_Samoa" title="Administrative divisions of American Samoa">3 districts and 2 atolls of American Samoa</a>, all of <a href="/wiki/Guam" title="Guam">Guam</a>, the 4 municipalities in the <a href="/wiki/Northern_Mariana_Islands" title="Northern Mariana Islands">Northern Mariana Islands</a>, and the 9 islands in the <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/U.S._Minor_Outlying_Islands" title="U.S. Minor Outlying Islands">U.S. Minor Outlying Islands</a>.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-CensusT_1-1"><a href="#cite_note-CensusT-1">[1]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-CensusCounties2_2-1"><a href="#cite_note-CensusCounties2-2">[2]</a></sup><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-USMOICounties_5-0"><a href="#cite_note-USMOICounties-5">[5]</a></sup> Like in the states, each county equivalent in the territories has its own INCITS/FIPS code. <a href="/wiki/American_Samoa" title="American Samoa">American Samoa</a> does have its <a href="/wiki/Administrative_divisions_of_American_Samoa" title="Administrative divisions of American Samoa">own counties</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-6"><a href="#cite_note-6">[6]</a></sup>, but the U.S. Census Bureau counts American Samoa's districts and atolls as counties.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-CensusCounties2_2-2"><a href="#cite_note-CensusCounties2-2">[2]</a></sup>
</p>
<div class="toc" id="toc"><div class="toctitle" dir="ltr" lang="en"><h2>Contents</h2></div>

<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Table">Table</span><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=List_of_United_States_counties_and_county_equivalents&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: Table">edit</a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></h2>
<p>The following <a href="/wiki/Help:Sorting" title="Help:Sorting">sortable</a> <a href="/wiki/Help:Table" title="Help:Table">table</a> lists the 3,242 <a href="/wiki/County_(United_States)" title="County (United States)">counties</a> and county equivalents of the United States with the following information for each entity:
</p>
<ol><li>The <a href="/wiki/International_Committee_for_Information_Technology_Standards" title="International Committee for Information Technology Standards">International Committee for Information Technology Standards</a> (INCITS) code (also known as <a href="/wiki/Federal_Information_Processing_Standard_state_code" title="Federal Information Processing Standard state code">FIPS code</a>)<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_4-1"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-4">[4]</a></sup></li>
<li>The entity name<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_4-2"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-4">[4]</a></sup></li>
<li>The state, <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">federal district</a> or <a href="/wiki/Territories_of_the_United_States" title="Territories of the United States">territory</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_4-3"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-4">[4]</a></sup></li>
<li>The population as of July 1, 2013, as estimated by United States Census Bureau<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-PopEstCounties_4-4"><a href="#cite_note-PopEstCounties-4">[4]</a></sup></li>
<li>The <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Core_Based_Statistical_Area" title="Core Based Statistical Area">Core Based Statistical Area</a> if designated by the <a href="/wiki/Office_of_Management_and_Budget" title="Office of Management and Budget">Office of Management and Budget</a><sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-OMB_13-01_7-0"><a href="#cite_note-OMB_13-01-7">[7]</a></sup></li>
<li>The <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Combined_Statistical_Area" title="Combined Statistical Area">Combined Statistical Area</a> if designated by the Office of Management and Budget<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-OMB_13-01_7-1"><a href="#cite_note-OMB_13-01-7">[7]</a></sup></li></ol>

<li id="cite_note-San_Francisco-16"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-San_Francisco_16-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/San_Francisco" title="San Francisco">City and County of San Francisco, California</a> has a fully <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county">consolidated city and county government</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Broomfield-17"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Broomfield_17-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Broomfield,_Colorado" title="Broomfield, Colorado">City and County of Broomfield, Colorado</a> has a fully <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county">consolidated city and county government</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Denver-18"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Denver_18-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Denver" title="Denver">City and County of Denver, Colorado</a> has a fully <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county">consolidated city and county government</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Nogov-19"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-2"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-3"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-4"><sup><i><b>e</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-5"><sup><i><b>f</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-6"><sup><i><b>g</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-7"><sup><i><b>h</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-8"><sup><i><b>i</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-9"><sup><i><b>j</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-10"><sup><i><b>k</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-11"><sup><i><b>l</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-12"><sup><i><b>m</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-13"><sup><i><b>n</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-14"><sup><i><b>o</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-15"><sup><i><b>p</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-16"><sup><i><b>q</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-17"><sup><i><b>r</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-18"><sup><i><b>s</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-19"><sup><i><b>t</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Nogov_19-20"><sup><i><b>u</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">This county has no functional county government.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-DC-20"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-DC_20-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/United_States_Census_Bureau" title="United States Census Bureau">United States Census Bureau</a> and the <a href="/wiki/Office_of_Management_and_Budget" title="Office of Management and Budget">Office of Management and Budget</a> consider the <a href="/wiki/Washington,_D.C." title="Washington, D.C.">District of Columbia</a> to be a <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/County_equivalent" title="County equivalent">county equivalent</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Honolulu-21"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Honolulu_21-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Honolulu_County,_Hawaii" title="Honolulu County, Hawaii">City and County of Honolulu, Hawaii</a> has a <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county">county government with municipal functions</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-NewOrleans-22"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-NewOrleans_22-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/New_Orleans" title="New Orleans">City of New Orleans and Orleans Parish, Louisiana</a> have a fully <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county">consolidated city and parish government</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Baltimore-23"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Baltimore_23-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Baltimore" title="Baltimore">City of Baltimore, Maryland</a> is an <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">independent city</a> exclusive of any county.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Nantucket-24"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Nantucket_24-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Nantucket,_Massachusetts" title="Nantucket, Massachusetts">Town and County of Nantucket, Massachusetts</a> has a fully <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county">consolidated town and county government</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-St._Louis-25"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-St._Louis_25-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/St._Louis" title="St. Louis">City of St. Louis, Missouri</a> is an <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">independent city</a> exclusive of any county.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Carson_City-26"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Carson_City_26-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Carson_City,_Nevada" title="Carson City, Nevada">Consolidated Municipality of Carson City, Nevada</a> is an <a href="/wiki/Independent_city_(United_States)" title="Independent city (United States)">independent city</a> exclusive of any county.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Los_Alamos-27"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Los_Alamos_27-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a href="/wiki/Los_Alamos_County,_New_Mexico" title="Los Alamos County, New Mexico">Los Alamos County, New Mexico</a> has a <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county">county government with municipal functions</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-Philly-28"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Philly_28-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">The <a href="/wiki/Philadelphia" title="Philadelphia">City of Philadelphia</a> and <a href="/wiki/Philadelphia_County,_Pennsylvania" title="Philadelphia County, Pennsylvania">Philadelphia County, Pennsylvania</a> have a fully <a class="mw-redirect" href="/wiki/Consolidated_city%E2%80%93county" title="Consolidated city–county">consolidated city and county government</a>.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-USMOI-29"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-USMOI_29-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a class="external free" href="http://www.statoids.com/uum.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.statoids.com/uum.html</a> Statoids.com. U.S. Minor Outlying Islands. Retrieved July 5, 2018.</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation news">Faulconer, Justin (July 1, 2013). <a class="external text" href="https://www.webcitation.org/6KWGSWPrA?url=http://www.newsadvance.com/news/local/article_5dcbc886-e1e9-11e2-a412-001a4bcf6878.html" rel="nofollow">"Bedford reversion to town becomes official today"</a>. <i>The News &amp; Advance</i>. </li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">On July 1, 2013, the former <a href="/wiki/Bedford,_Virginia" title="Bedford, Virginia">City of Bedford</a> gave up its city charter and became a town within Bedford County.<sup class="reference" id="cite_ref-30"><a href="#cite_note-30">[30]</a></sup> Population estimates are combined totals for the political entities that existed before the merger.</span>
</li>

<div aria-labelledby="United_States_Census" class="navbox" role="navigation" style="padding:3px"><table class="nowraplinks hlist collapsible autocollapse navbox-inner" style="border-spacing:0;background:transparent;color:inherit"><tbody><tr><th class="navbox-title" colspan="2" scope="col"><div class="plainlinks hlist navbar mini"><ul><li class="nv-view"><a href="/wiki/Template:USCensus_Geography" title="Template:USCensus Geography"><abbr style=";;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;" title="View this template">v</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-talk"><a href="/wiki/Template_talk:USCensus_Geography" title="Template talk:USCensus Geography"><abbr style=";;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;" title="Discuss this template">t</abbr></a></li><li class="nv-edit"><a class="external text" href="//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Template:USCensus_Geography&amp;action=edit"><abbr style=";;background:none transparent;border:none;-moz-box-shadow:none;-webkit-box-shadow:none;box-shadow:none;" title="Edit this template">e</abbr></a></li></ul></div><div id="United_States_Census" style="font-size:114%;margin:0 4em"><a href="/wiki/United_States_Census" title="United States Census">United States Census</a></div></th></tr><tr><th class="navbox-group" scope="row" style="width:1%">Regions</th><td class="navbox-list navbox-odd" style="text-align:left;border-left-width:2px;border-left-style:solid;width:100%;padding:0px"><div style="padding:0em 0.25em">
<ul><li><a href="/wiki/Census_division" title="Census division">Division</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/U.S._state" title="U.S. state">State</a></li>
